medical_history.chief_complaint: Nausea, bilateral flank pain, and urinary retention.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The symptoms progressed with a background of recurrent urinary tract infections since age six, and episodes of constipation treated with MiraLAX. Voiding dysfunction has been previously managed with biofeedback and pelvic floor muscle training exercises.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Recurrent urinary tract infections since age six; history of constipation treated with MiraLAX; voiding dysfunction; left-sided grade 3 vesicoureteral reflux; right-sided grade 1 vesicoureteral reflux; potentially narrowed segment in the membranous urethra identified at age seven; severe bilateral hydroureteronephrosis and irregular bladder contour noted on renal ultrasound at age 13; diagnosed with Hinman syndrome; psychological history included anxiety, depression, obsessive-compulsive disorder, and attention-deficit hyperactivity syndrome.
